    "Evaluation": {
      "text": "Middle ear fluid cultures\nCT mastoid with IV contrast\n90% sensitive\nDelineates extent of bony involvement\nHelps to diagnosis\nabscess\nformation",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "abscess",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Abscess"
        }
      ]
    },
    "Management": {
      "text": "ENT consultation - cases refractory to parenteral antibiotics may require surgical irrigation and debridement with possible mastoidectomy.\nCoverage against\nS. pneumoniae\n, S. pyogenes,\nS. aureus\n,\nH. influenzae\nClindamycin\n600mg IV q8 hours\nOR\n(if\nMRSA\nconcern use\nVancomycin\nregimen)\nVancomycin\n15-20mg/kg IV q12 hours\nPLUS\nCeftriaxone\n1g (50mg/kg) IV once daily\nOR\nAmpicillin/Sulbactam\n3g (50mg/kg) IV q6 hours\nIf chronic or severe, need pseudomonas coverage\nVanco\n+\nPiperacillin-tazobactam\n(Zosyn) 100mg/kg/dose piperacillin IV q6h (max 4g piperacillin/dose)",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
